An argument over a room in an abandoned building led to the death of seven people &nbsp;in the Johannesburg CBD.&nbsp; Seven others were rushed to hospital with serious injuries. The fire is believed to have started at 9am and allegations are that everything began when two people argued over a room and one of then started the fire in anger. Tell a friendSeven people died when a man arguing over a room allegedly started a fire in an abandoned building in the CBD. There was chaos as the fire spread and some people rushed out of the burning structure. Others used their bedding as a makeshift rope to escape the deadly flames. Some rushed on the top of the building and fire fighters had to use an extended ladder to save them and bring them down to safety. The abandoned building, was allegedly home to drug users and sex workers and was a problem for the neighboring businesses. Johannesburg Emergency Services spokesperson, Nana Radebe, said the cause of the fire was still now known. She also said that the victims of the tragedy had also not been identified and the process of identification could only take place after the preliminary investigation. Radebe also said over 40 people had been rescued from the building. There was chaos as the fire spread and some people rushed out of the burning structure. Others used their bedding as a makeshift rope to escape the deadly flames. Some rushed on the top of the building and fire fighters had to use an extended ladder to save them and bring them down to safety. The abandoned building, was allegedly home to drug users and sex workers and was a problem for the neighboring businesses. Johannesburg Emergency Services spokesperson, Nana Radebe, said the cause of the fire was still now known. She also said that the victims of the tragedy had also not been identified and the process of identification could only take place after the preliminary investigation. Radebe also said over 40 people had been rescued from the building.